cs.SC, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.GR

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithmic methods for computing Puiseux series expansions for algebraic surfaces. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as the paper uses a polyhedral method to compute cones of normal vectors to the Newton polytopes of the given polynomial system that defines the surface. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper outlines an algorithmic approach to compute Puiseux series expansions. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the solution sets of polynomial systems. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is the least likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with algebraic surfaces, which can be visualized in graphics.
